1.title: Herkimer Graduate
1.plot: Blackcatloner celebrates his long-awaited graduation from Herkimer College as well as upgrading his website to a dot-com site.

2.title: Hey, Stella! You're Making Me Crazy
2.plot: As he celebrates the increase in traffic to his website and getting his first-ever smartphone, Blackcatloner rants about Daylight Savings Time and finds himself snowed in when Winter Storm Stella comes to Herkimer.

3.title: Happy Anniversary, Blackcatloner.com
3.plot: As he continues to adjust to life with a smartphone, Blackcatloner celebrates the 10-year anniversary of his website Blackcatloner.com. At the same time, he resolves to get healthy.

4.title: The Last Week of Work Workout
4.plot: As he gets closer to his last week at work before vacation, Blackcatloner reacts to the final trailer for the upcoming Spider-Man: Homecoming as well as the teaser trailer for the remake of It. Also as part of his quest to get healthier, he decides to start working out again.

5.title: Vacation!
5.plot: Blackcatloner celebrates his vacation from work by starting a new workout routine courtesy of a new app on his smartphone. Also he finds time to do a mini-review of Suicide Squad and makes a return trip to the Canal Trail. And he could not have picked a better time to go on vacation because he has gorgeous weather to enjoy.

6.title: The Last Jedi Wears a Cat Mask!
6.plot: Blackcatloner reacts to the first trailer for the eagerly-anticipated Star Wars movie, The Last Jedi. Also he encounters the messiest burger he ever had and shows off his new favorite viral video where a guy dresses up in a cat mask. And in the midst of all of this, he considers returning to his hometown of Red Hook for his 20-year reunion.

7.title: Murder of a Herkimer County Teacher by Dennis Webster
7.plot: In the latest installment of the Blackcat Book Club, Blackcatloner spotlights a true crime story from a local author about a historic Central New York murder case.

8.title: Time for Something New
8.plot: Blackcatloner comes to a decision in regards to his future on YouTube.

1.title: Blackcatloner Reviews Indiana Jones and the Kingdom of the Crystal Skull
1.plot: Blackcatloner makes his official debut on YouTube with a review of the long-awaited Indiana Jones sequel, Indiana Jones and the Kingdom of the Crystal Skull.

2.title: The Librarian
2.plot: Blackcatloner meets a sexy librarian (played by YouTube star LisaNova.)

3.title: A Funny Thing Happened on the Way to the Ilion Little Theater Club
3.plot: Blackcatloner exposes one of the Mohawk Valley's best-kept secrets: The Ilion Little Theater Club.

4.title: Gay Teen Sues Mohawk School District
4.plot: Blackcatloner tries his hand at doing news stories by talking about a woman supposedly pulling a fertility pill scam. In addition, he also talks about the release of the Pan Am Flight 103 bomber and an uplifting story of a gay teen who decides to sue a local school district for failing to protect him from bullies.

6.title: Calling Mr. Safety
6.plot: See what happens when Blackcatloner decides to call the man who influenced his YouTube career: Mr. Safety.

1.title: A Walk Through Herkimer
1.plot: After a long and pointless night at work, Blackcatloner decides to take his viewers on a little tour of his town of Herkimer, NY. He also shares a weird story about a historic jail.

2.title: With Great Power...
2.plot: After a horrible week at his real job, Blackcatloner talks about his life on the Internet.

11.title: At Year's End
11.plot: As 2010 draws to a close, Blackcatloner talks about what's coming up in the year ahead and finds time to bash Justin Beiber.

1.title: Best Song to Have Sex To
1.plot: In the latest Q and A installment, Blackcatloner answers some more questions including what he thinks is the best song for getting it on.

9.title: Blackcatloner Meets the Italian Stallion
9.plot: Blackcatloner takes a trip to the Boxing Hall of Fame to see Rocky star Sylvester Stallone and Mike Tyson's induction ceremony.

1.title: I Wanna Be the Sexiest Zombie Alive!
1.plot: Blackcatloner returns from a year-long hiatus to do another Q and A vlog where he answers questions about zombies, women and more.

1.title: New Year's Vlog 2013
1.plot: Blackcatloner rings in 2013 by talking about how he plans to take his videos in a new direction.

2.title: Twilight Ruined My Relationship!
2.plot: Blackcatloner talks about how the much-maligned Twilight franchise has been blamed for ending relationships and marriages.

3.title: To Russia/Ukraine/Asia/Etc. for Love
3.plot: Blackcatloner explores the dating phenomenon about how American men are looking to foreign women for relationships and marriage.

8.title: The Librarian: 5th Anniversary Edition
8.plot: It's the remastered edition of the 2008 Blackcatloner/LisaNova collaboration video, now with a new music track.

10.title: Blackcat in the City
10.plot: Blackcatloner talks about a recent day trip he took to New York City.

11.title: Flood!
11.plot: Blackcatloner rants about a recent storm that left Herkimer almost completely flooded while he was at work.

13.title: Blackcatloner's Top 5 Favorite Christmas Movies
13.plot: Christmas time is here which means presents, peace on Earth and of course, Christmas movies, which is why Blackcatloner is counting down his top 5 favorite Christmas movies.

1.title: Blackcatloner on Super Bowl 49
1.plot: Blackcatloner dishes out his thoughts on Super Bowl 49 which includes thoughts on the controversy surrounding the New England Patriots to Katy Perry's halftime show to the depressing Super Bowl commercial lineup.

2.title: What Back to the Future Part 2 Got Right- and Wrong- About 2015
2.plot: Since 2015 is upon us, Blackcatloner talks about the predictions that the movie Back to the Future Part II got right- and wrong- about this year.

3.title: I Can Has 100 Videos!
3.plot: To celebrate his 100th video upload to YouTube despite taking him several years to accomplish this, Blackcatloner decides to do a compilation of the previous 99 videos.

4.title: A Thing About Introverts
4.plot: Blackcatloner talks about the struggles that introverted people like himself face in today's world, which is predominately extroverted.

5.title: Revival by Stephen King
5.plot: Blackcatloner debuts the Blackcat Book Club segment with a look at the Stephen King novel, Revival.

6.title: How to Survive on YouTube
6.plot: Blackcatloner offers some pointers for those who are looking to get into the world of online video making.

7.title: Blackcatloner on Star Wars: Episode 7 Teaser Trailer
7.plot: Blackcatloner reacts to the first teaser trailer for the long-awaited latest installment in the Star Wars saga.

8.title: Ghostbusters, Star Wars and Frozen 2... Oh, My!
8.plot: In this segment of Fanboy News, Blackcatloner talks about news involving a Ghostbusters Cinematic Universe and while talking about the upcoming Frozen sequel, rants about it's continued popularity.

9.title: 2014- A Look Back
9.plot: As he heads into 2015, Blackcatloner takes a look back at 2014.

11.title: I Will Not Pay to Online Date!
11.plot: Blackcatloner does a dating rant about why people should not pay on dating sites.

12.title: Blackcatloner on Star Wars: Episode 7 and Batman vs. Superman Teaser Trailer
12.plot: Blackcatloner takes a look at the teaser trailers for not one, but two eagerly-anticipated movies. First, he takes a look at the second teaser trailer for Star Wars: The Force Awakens which features an appearance from two old friends. Then he reviews the first teaser trailer for Batman vs. Superman: Dawn of Justice where he gets to see the first appearance of Batfleck.

15.title: You Just Entered the Friend Zone!
15.plot: It's dating rant time as Blackcatloner talks about what happens when guys end up in the dreaded "Friend Zone" while trying to get a girlfriend.

16.title: Once More Unto the Breach and Goodbye, Blip
16.plot: As he prepares for his final semester at Herkimer College, Blackcatloner discusses the drama surrounding his financial aid as well as saying goodbye to Blip, a site he used to distribute videos to in the past before they unceremoniously dismissed him due to lack of promotion.

17.title: An Ode to My Childhood
17.plot: Blackcatloner takes a trip down memory lane as he recalls his life growing up in Red Hook, New York during the 80's and 90's. Along the way, he shows everyone a life where technology, reality shows and social media was replaced by drive-in movies, lusting after female cartoon characters and everything that made the 80's great.

18.title: Where Was I on 9/11?
18.plot: As the anniversary of 9/11 approaches, Blackcatloner uses that time to do a Legends of the Blackcat installment about what he was doing on that tragic day.

19.title: Enter the Blackcatloner: My YouTube Story
19.plot: In honor of YouTube's tenth anniversary, Blackcatloner recounts the origin story of how he first became involved with the world of social media and his experiences as being one lone cat against a big bad world on YouTube.

20.title: Not Another Star Wars Update!
20.plot: As the date for the new Star Wars movie gets closer, Blackcatloner reviews the official movie poster for The Force Awakens and reacts to the final trailer for the movie.

21.title: What's the Deal with Frozen?
21.plot: After initially dismissing the movie Frozen as Disney's answer to Twilight and especially after being subjected to repeat showings of it eight hours a day at his real job, Blackcatloner is influenced to do a film editorial to see why Frozen is still popular two years after its release to theaters.

1.title: A Year of Progress and a Look Ahead
1.plot: As the year 2015 comes to a close, Blackcatloner reflects on the past year which he sees as a year of progress and he takes a look ahead at what's coming in 2016.

2.title: Doctor Sleep by Stephen King
2.plot: Blackcatloner does his latest Blackcat Book Club installment on yet another book by the Master himself, Stephen King: Doctor Sleep, the sequel to his acclaimed novel The Shining.

3.title: Movie Madness
3.plot: Blackcatloner is inspired by an old newspaper article from his local newspaper to talk about movies to fit the mood of everyone from every walk of life.

4.title: Blackcatloner's Top 10 Favorite Movies of All Time
4.plot: Blackcatloner counts down his top 10 favorite movies of all time.

5.title: Hatin' on Utica Datin'
5.plot: Blackcatloner once again turns an old newspaper article into a video. This time out it's a dating rant where a male and female reporter offer opposing views on the dating scene in Utica. Blackcatloner ultimately finds that the female reporter has a more sensible view than her male counterpart.

6.title: Re: What the Hell, YouTube?
6.plot: Blackcatloner responds to Doug Walker's rant about how the Channel Awesome YouTube channel was hit with copyright strikes and how some of his channel's privileges were revoked. He also talks about the history of YouTube in the early days and recounts his experiences with copyright claims for his Blackcat Riffs show.

7.title: The Seven Percent Solution by Nicholas Meyer
7.plot: Want to know what Sherlock Holmes has in common with Star Trek? Find out on this installment of the Blackcat Book Club when Blackcatloner looks at a Sherlock Holmes novel that was written by the same man who directed one of the best films in the Star Trek franchise.

8.title: Star Wars: Episode 8 and Suicide Squad
8.plot: Blackcatloner brings back his Fanboy News segment from last year and talks about the next installment in the new Star Wars trilogy as well as more news about Suicide Squad.

9.title: A Very #Puppymonkeybaby Super Bowl
9.plot: It's Super Bowl time again and you know what that means, right? It's time for Blackcatloner to offer his thoughts on Super Bowl 50 between the Denver Broncos and the Carolina Panthers. Overall, he felt that the game and the commercials this year were a big improvement over the previous Super Bowl. But at the same time, he was bored with the very controversial Halftime Show.

10.title: Rogue One, Power Rangers, Turtles 2
10.plot: In Fanboy News, Blackcatloner delivers more news about the upcoming Star Wars spinoff, Rogue One as well as the upcoming Ninja Turtles sequel and the Power Rangers reboot.

11.title: Kids These Days
11.plot: Blackcatloner is appalled at the state of today's society and rants about the sense of entitlement that today's youth seem to have and also rants about how today's media ranging from the endless movie reboots to horrible reality shows to the horrible music led to the collapse of America's youth.

12.title: Blackcatloner Tries the BK Grilled Dog and the Oreo Irish Mint Shake
12.plot: For lunch, Blackcatloner heads to Burger King to try their new line of hot dogs as well as their answer to McDonald's Shamrock Shake.

13.title: Re: Where's the Fair Use?
13.plot: Blackcatloner responds to the Nostalgia Critic's rant about YouTube's broken copyright system and asks the one question that's on everyone's mind: Where's the fair use?

14.title: More R-Rated Comic Book Movies?! Yes, Please!
14.plot: With the recent success of the R-Rated comic book movie Deadpool, it would seem natural that more movies would jump on the bandwagon. Blackcatloner explores that in this installment of Fanboy News.

15.title: The Breakfast Club
15.plot: As a continuation of his rant on the state of America's youth, Blackcatloner does a film editorial of the iconic 80's teen comedy The Breakfast Club and applies the issues in this movie to today's society.

16.title: Red Hook High School Drifter
16.plot: It's time for another trip into Blackcatloner's secret past as he talks about his high school years as a student at Red Hook High School during the mid-90's.

17.title: How I Spent My YouTube Vacation/Star Trek Beyond Review
17.plot: Blackcatloner returns from another unintentional hiatus from making videos by talking about how he spent his time off from going to WWE Live to dealing with more copyright drama. Also he finds time to review the latest voyage of the crew of the Starship Enterprise.

18.title: Blackcatloner in Puerto Rico
18.plot: In this Legends of the Blackcat installment, Blackcatloner recalls his Spanish class trip to Puerto Rico during his junior year of high school in the mid-90's. And yes, he tells tales of getting lost in Old San Juan, girls in bikinis and almost not getting back in the boat during a snorkeling trip.

19.title: Change Is in the Air
19.plot: Blackcatloner decides to return to old-school video making by taking a little trip to the Erie Canal Trail and along the way, he celebrates the return of Crystal Pepsi, discovers an obscure 80's TV series and rants about YouTube's latest censorship policy.

20.title: Yo, Adrian! It's the Rocky Retrospective, Y'know?
20.plot: Since 2016 marks the 40th anniversary of the release of the original Rocky movie, Blackcatloner takes a look at the Italian Stallion's movie career. From the greatness of the first two movies to the over-the-top silliness of Rockys 3 and 4 to the sheer horror of Rocky V to the redemption of Rocky Balboa and the rebirth of the franchise with Creed.

21.title: 10 Years a Social Media Junkie
21.plot: As he prepares for inventory week at his job, Blackcatloner reflects on ten years of blogging and even jokes about iconic Star Trek actor George Takei coming to his town.

22.title: Goodwill Hunting
22.plot: Blackcatloner obsesses over pumpkin spice lattes, hot girls in yoga pants and donates some of his old things to Goodwill.

23.title: Mr. Mercedes and the Perks of Life Vlogging
23.plot: Blackcatloner talks about the concept of daily vlogging and why he only does it weekly. Also he spotlights the wildly-popular Mr. Mercedes trilogy by Stephen King on the Blackcat Book Club.

24.title: Life's Too Short for a Fall Heat Wave
24.plot: Blackcatloner talks about everything from the controversial 2016 Presidential Election to some upcoming movies. Also a fall heat wave allows him to go out and show off some of Central New York's famous fall scenery.

25.title: Ghosts of Halloween Past
25.plot: As Halloween approaches, Blackcatloner reviews a certain controversial ghost-related reboot where the walk home from the college was more interesting than the movie. At the same time, he also offers another Legends of the Blackcat tale about his Halloweens growing up in Red Hook. Also he recalls the time he walked through a haunted cornfield while a student at Herkimer College.

26.title: Election Day Is Here Again
26.plot: The moment America and the world has been dreading has finally arrived in Herkimer: The 2016 Presidential Election. And of course, Blackcatloner has his thoughts on it.

27.title: Snow Is Back Along with Some Unfinished Business
27.plot: Blackcatloner talks about everything from getting sick to snow returning to Central New York and he offers an update on college.

-1.title: Jesus, Bro! Review/RIP Batman
-1.plot: In this latest podcast, Blackcatlone reviews Internet reviewer Brad Jones' religious spoof movie Jesus, Bro. Also he talks about losing childhood icons Roger Moore and Batman star Adam West. And he also talks about living alone after his sister moves out of his house.

imdb.title: Blackcatloner
plot: Join Internet blogger _Blackcatloner_ (qv) as he vlogs about random things going on in his life, as well as movie reviews and other topics close to his heart proving that he is "one lone cat against a big bad world."::Tim Haines
